                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; incipit of Text
                           I; directives to the ministers; abbreviations of the directives yǝbǝl
                           kāhǝn “the priest says”, yǝbǝl diyāqon “the deacon says”; yǝbǝl ḥǝzb “the
                           people say”; titles of books to be read; initial line of the readings;
                           incipit of Text II; the word “bārǝkanna… “bless us…” in Text II; notes
                           written in the upper margin; elements of the punctuation signs; elements
                           of Ethiopic numerals. &#xD; On the incipit page of Text I (fols. 5r), a
                           few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
